reviews.text:
Went here during my trip to Hong Kong. The hotel was decent. It wasn't in the best part of Hong Kong. But you have public transport to get around that. 

The hotel and the room itself was nice and clean. The bathroom and the utilities were also in good condition and my particular room had a small wall safe in it. Which you could set your own code for.  

The room didn't have a view, but again this is inner city. So it doesn't matter. It did have air conditioning which was good and the bed was massive for a double bed and comfortable. All in all a great experience and if I needed a hotel again. I would come back here.

Good no nonsense service.  Good the price i paid.   Bathroom was too small and could have been cleaner.  Location very good within 10 walks to major shopping districts and transport.  Pictures of view from room on L19

The rooms are very small, there's barely enough space to open your luggage flat on the ground. The beds are shorter than the standard size, if you are above average in height, your feet will dangle off the edge.
Business hotel locates near Olympic Station.  Comparatively spaeaking, it is good for people having a short trip in HK.

Ugliest service ever. Staffs are rude. Arrogant hotel receptionist. Room is not fully equipped with the essential things you need when travelling such as the socket outlet etc. You are the guest but they doesn’t respect you, which I think is a basic manner in any humankind. Your money isn’t worth it here.
